  "title" : "Getting wrong locale for Portuguese (Brazil)",
  "body" : "<p>I am trying to get system locale for Portuguese (Brazil), but it is giving the decimal separator as <code>.</code> instead of <code>,</code> Can anyone please help on that? I am using Java 8.</p>\n<p>Below is the code I am using:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>public static void main(String[] args) \n{\n    final Locale locale = new Locale(System.getProperty(&quot;user.country.format&quot;));\n    \n    final NumberFormat nf = NumberFormat.getNumberInstance(locale);\n     \n    DecimalFormatSymbols decSymbols = new DecimalFormatSymbols(locale);\n    System.out.println(&quot;Decimal Symbol&quot;+ decSymbols.getDecimalSeparator() + &quot;&quot;);\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Getting decimal separator as <code>.</code> instead of <code>,</code>.</p>\n"
}